1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,250
Prototypes are fundamental to JavaScript's memory-efficient method sharing across instances

2
00:00:06,638 --> 00:00:07,513
In classes

3
00:00:07,675 --> 00:00:10,537
static methods enable shared functionality

4
00:00:10,887 --> 00:00:13,312
distinct from instance-specific methods

5
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:15,725
Unlike traditional prototype methods

6
00:00:15,975 --> 00:00:18,712
static methods are called on the class itself

7
00:00:19,137 --> 00:00:20,438
rather than its instances

8
00:00:20,837 --> 00:00:25,225
This distinction is crucial for actions pertinent to the class as a whole

9
00:00:25,663 --> 00:00:27,825
rather than any individual instance

10
00:00:28,225 --> 00:00:29,925
By leveraging static methods

11
00:00:30,275 --> 00:00:34,013
developers can encapsulate class-specific behavior cohesively

